    "created_at": "2015-01-06T22:41:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-06T22:41:02Z",
    "body": "Are you using the latest atom-shell? I believe code related to `--touch-events` and `--touch-devices` is already in atom-shell.\n\nCan you try appending `--touch-events=invalid` in command line and see if there is a `Invalid --touch-events option: invalid` error printed? If it does not then you are using an old atom-shell that doesn't support this switch.\n\n> Is there any reason to just not enable it all the time?\n\nI think it will convert all mouse events into touch events.\n"
  },
