    "created_at": "2015-04-14T07:02:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-04-14T07:02:02Z",
    "body": "As it is described in details at atom/atom#6306, atom editor since version 0.189.0 suffers from a Chrome41 bug with touch screen in Linux@VirtualBox environment. I have tried:\n- passing option(s) `--touch-devices=123` and/or `--touch-events=invalid` to atom command line directly;\n- modifying `/usr/bin/atom` to pass the options above;\n- patching source code with `app.commandLine.appendSwitch '--touch-events=123'` and rebuilding the editor from the scratch.\n\nNothing helped.\n"
